ice in the dark for 30 minutes. This is enough for about 15 tests. <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Note:<\/span><span>\u00a0BioLegend fluorophore-conjugated streptavidin products are recommended. For 30 \u00b5L\u00a0of fixed peptide Flex-T\u2122 monomer, we suggest using 3.3 \u00b5L\u00a0of BioLegend PE Streptavidin (Cat. No.\u00a0<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.biolegend.com\/en-us\/products\/pe-streptavidin-1475\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">405203<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">) or APC Streptavidin (Cat. No.\u00a0<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.biolegend.com\/en-us\/products\/apc-streptavidin-1470\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">405207<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">). For BV421\u2122 Streptavidin (Cat. No.\u00a0<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.biolegend.com\/en-us\/products\/brilliant-violet-421-streptavidin-7297\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">405225<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">), use 1.3 \u00b5L. For oligo\u00a0<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.biolegend.com\/en-us\/search-results?Keywords=totalseq%20streptavidin&k1=totalseq,total-seq,total%20seq,proteogenomics,ADT,oligo-antibody,oligo%20antibody,oligo-antibodies,oligo%20antibodies,oligonucleotide%20conjugated%20antibodies&k2=streptavidin,Streptavidin-APC\/Cy7\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">barcoded<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">\u00a0Streptavidin reagents please use 1.3 \u00b5L. For optimal reaction with other fluorophore-conjugated Streptavidin products, ensure that the monomer:streptavidin conjugate has a 5:1 ~ 6:1 molar ratio. (For our full choice of Streptavidin conjugates, visit our <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.biolegend.com\/en-us\/streptavidin-conjugates\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">Streptavidin Conjugates webpage<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">. Note that purified, biotinylated, HRP-Streptavidin and\u00a0MojoSort\u2122\u00a0and Ultra Streptavidin (USA) kits are not recommended for this procedure.)<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":968294,"guid":"E4F04950B66B11EAB640DFB0D1FC903F","previous_id":968284,"previous_guid":"773F6260B66B11EAB640DFB0D1FC903F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"55D0AF3107B74BFA885EF010EC509F80","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Generation of Tetramers:"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B103A65DA0534155BCADED325C8C35C2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Incubate the tubes or sealed plates at 2-8\u00b0C overnight (or on ice for 30 minutes in the dark, if staining needs to be performed immediately). <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Tip:<\/span><span>\u00a0We recommend Flex-T\u2122 to be assembled with two different streptavidin conjugates in separate reactions. This allows for two-color staining with the same tetramer allele, ensuring the highest specificity.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":968296,"guid":"EA265CC0B66B11EAB640DFB0D1FC903F","previous_id":968309,"previous_guid":"363F4220B66C11EAB640DFB0D1FC903F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5A4DCB6CFD30487A80B19A29A5A8B3B1","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"